             <settlement>New York City</settlement>
            </address>
        </dateline>
        <salute>Dear <persName ref="#Parsons">Betty</persName>;</salute>
      </opener>

       
        <div type="body">
          <p>This is to confirm our <del rend="overstrike">telephone</del>conversation
            <lb/>about<persName ref="#Pollock">Jackson Pollock</persName>.I am very pleased that you are going to
            <lb/>take him on in your gallery and give him a show next winter.
            <lb/>From now on he will bring his work to you and you will sell it
            <lb/>taking the usual one third discount and remitting the other
            <lb/>two thirds of the sales to me. Before leaving I will send you
            <lb/>some of his unsold paintings of the past few years and I will
            <lb/>give you all the data necessary concerning him whenever you
            <lb/>like. Please let me know when I can send the paintings to you.
            <lb/>Either late May or the first days of June.
          </p>
        </div>

        
        <closer>
          <salute>Yours sincerely,</salute>
          <signed>
            <lb/><persName ref="#Guggenheim">Peggy Guggenheim</persName>
          </signed>
          </closer>

